Skolar 2.0 – Tutor App developed by fullcircle

A university project demonstrating a tutor-matching app with a login screen on startup, Google SSO + Email/Password authentication (Firebase Auth), a bottom-nav UI, and a working Tutors list fetched from Firestore via REST (no paid services required). Non-implemented tabs show “Feature to be implemented”.

Features:

Auth
- LoginScreen on startup (Google SSO + Email/Password sign-in & sign-up)
- Settings: show current user, Sign out, Revoke Google access, Send password reset email (for email/password users)

Navigation
- Bottom navigation: Home, Tutors (working), Bookings (TBI), Messages (TBI), Settings

Tutors (working feature)
- Reads tutors from Cloud Firestore via REST using OkHttp + Gson

Booking (working feature)
- book tutoring lessons

Settings (working feature_
- change language

Educational Content (working feature)
- access educational content

Architect:

app/
  src/main/
    AndroidManifest.xml
    java/com/example/skolar20/
      MainActivity.kt                 // sets content -> App()
      SkolarApp.kt                    // Application class
      navigation/
        NavDestinations.kt
        NavGraph.kt                   // routes/tabs
      ui/
        App.kt                        // Auth gate (Login vs Main app + bottom nav)
        screens/
          LoginScreen.kt              // Google SSO + Email/Password
          SettingsScreen.kt           // account actions + local settings
          HomeScreen.kt               // quick nav
          TutorsScreen.kt             // REST read from Firestore
          ComingSoonScreen.kt         // placeholder for TBI features
      data/
        model/Tutor.kt
        remote/FirestoreService.kt    // OkHttp + Gson Firestore REST
  build.gradle.kts                    // app module gradle (deps, BuildConfig fields)
build.gradle.kts                      // root plugins (AGP, Kotlin, Google services)
settings.gradle.kts                   // repositories (google(), mavenCentral())
